Sinohydro Group Ltd. (601669) , Chinaâ€™s
biggest builder of hydroelectric dams, reported a 28.4 percent
increase in the value of contracts signed in the first quarter.  The contracts totaled 42.8 billion  yuan  ($7 billion) from
January to March, compared with 33.4 billion yuan a year
earlier, Sinohydro said today in a  statement  to the Shanghai
stock exchange. About 51 percent of the contracts were in China.  Of those, domestic water and hydroelectric projects were
